Adjust the blocks to swap based on your VRAM, this is a tradeoff between speed and memory usage.


IMPORTANT!
When at least 1 VACE block is swapped, the intermediate outputs are also offloaded reducing VRAM usage considerably
While the WanVideo 1.3B model is in FP32, the VACE module in it is in BF16, so using fp16_fast is technically lossy, but seems to be fine if you want the speed boost.

Original model link, you can rename to whatever you like:

[https://huggingface.co/ali-vilab/VACE-Wan2.1-1.3B-Preview/blob/main/diffusion_pytorch_model.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/ali-vilab/VACE-Wan2.1-1.3B-Preview/blob/main/diffusion_pytorch_model.safetensors)

fp8_fast seems to cause quality degradation

fp_16_fast enables "Full FP16 Accmumulation in FP16 GEMMs" feature available in the very latest pytorch nightly, this is around 20% speed boost. 

Sageattn if you have it installed can be used for almost double inference speed

You can also use the VACE as separate module with any normal matching size T2V model (not Fun models):

There are multiple ways to use control signal:

- with start frame + control frames:
  when you already have stylized first frame

- control frames + reference
  when your input image is not the exact first frame

- all at same time
  when you want extra boost to the likeness
If you have Triton installed, connect this for ~30% speed increase

We use an audio fearture to control the scale of the head, but any feature source can be used and they are all interchangable. "Drawable" feature is example below, but other feature sources include, but are not limited to:

midi
motion
time
depth
color
proximity
brightness
area
Whisper
etc.
